  <compounddef id="RAD" kind="page">
    <compoundname>RAD</compoundname>
    <title>RAD Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">RAD(real-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Converts an angle from <bold>degrees</bold> to <bold>radians</bold>. The result is a real number.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect1 id="RAD_1examples-85_1s1"><sect2 id="RAD_1examples-85_1s2"><sect3 id="RAD_1examples-85">
<title>Examples</title><para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>RAD(180)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces approximately <computeroutput>3.14159</computeroutput> (<computeroutput>PI#</computeroutput>).</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>RAD(90)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces approximately <computeroutput>1.570796</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Round-trip<sp/>conversion</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">angle#<sp/>=<sp/>270</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Radians<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>RAD(angle#)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Degrees<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>DEG(RAD(angle#))</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
<sect1 id="RAD_1notes-84_1s1"><sect2 id="RAD_1notes-84_1s2"><sect3 id="RAD_1notes-84">
<title>Notes</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Conversion formula: <computeroutput>radians = degrees * PI / 180</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Returned as a real value.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Useful for trigonometric functions (<ref refid="SIN" kindref="compound">SIN</ref>, <ref refid="COS" kindref="compound">COS</ref>, <ref refid="TAN" kindref="compound">TAN</ref>), which all expect input in radians.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
